Classification.Comment: The 2q32.3q33.1 deletion interval involves multiple genes, including SATB2 (OMIM 608148). Copy number deletions of or point variations in SATB2 cause Glass syndrome (GLASS; OMIM 612313). This syndrome is characterized by intellectual disability, severe speech problems, dental abnormalities, other abnormalities of the head and face (craniofacial anomalies), and behavioral problems (Rosenfeld et al.,PLoS One. 2009 Aug 10;4(8):e6568. PMID: 19668335; Balasubramanian et al., J Med Genet. 2011 May;48(5):290-8. PMID: 21343628; Leoyklang et al., Hum Genet. 2013 Dec;132(12):1383-93. PMID: 23925499; Gregoric Kumperscak et al., J Int Med Res. 2016 Apr;44(2):395-402. PMID:26811410).
